               <p>JAMES SCRUBY. I am a <rs id="t18260914-240-viclabel1376" type="occupation">baker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-240-victim1340 t18260914-240-viclabel1376"></join>, and live at No. 3, William-street, Curtain-road. On the 19th of July I was in the <placeName id="t18260914-240-crimeloc1377">Shepherdess-fields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-240-crimeloc1377" type="placeName" value="Shepherdess-fields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-240-crimeloc1377" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-240-off1374 t18260914-240-crimeloc1377"></join> with a tin of cakes, and a green cloth; I suppose there were two hundred young people about there - a young man was there with pies, and one of the persons came and asked for a penny pie; they seized hold of him, and threatened to throw him into the canal; I made the best of my way home, they ran after me, and asked me for change for a 6d. - I said "I could not give it," then the prisoner came up, and they all took my cakes together - after the prisoner had got some, he asked another, who had a pocket full, to give him one.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. CRESWELL. Q. What time was this? A. About half-past nine o'clock; I was afraid to take him that night; it was just twilight; I had seen him once before; I went up again on the Thursday evening with a friend or two - the prisoner came up, and the first thing I saw him do was to take a pair of boots - the officer<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182609140110"></xptr>came to ask me if I had been robbed - the prisoner was taken on the Friday evening; I have seen the prisoner's father; I did not say to him, that if he would pay me 15s., I would make such a representation, that the Grand Jury should throw the bill out; I did not intend anything dishonest, but they were always at my house; they were willing to give me money, but I would not accept of it till the trial was over.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18260914-240-verdict1378" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18260914-240-verdict1378" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
